{"id":"274645063_Discrete_Uncertainty_Principles_and_Sparse_Signal_Processing","abstract":"We develop new discrete uncertainty principles in terms of numerical\nsparsity, which is a continuous proxy for the 0-norm. Unlike traditional\nsparsity, the continuity of numerical sparsity naturally accommodates functions\nwhich are nearly sparse. After studying these principles and the functions that\nachieve exact or near equality in them, we identify certain consequences in a\nnumber of sparse signal processing applications.","authors":["Afonso S. Bandeira","Megan E. Lewis","Dustin G. Mixon"],"meta":["August 2018Journal of Fourier Analysis and Applications 24(4)","DOI:10.1007/s00041-017-9550-x","SourcearXiv"],"references":["264122919_Euclid_in_a_Taxicab_Sparse_Blind_Deconvolution_with_Smoothed_Regularization","263163731_Derandomizing_Restricted_Isometries_via_the_Legendre_Symbol","325514029_A_mathematical_introduction_to_compressive_sensing","283111925_An_Improved_Estimate_in_the_Restricted_Isometry_Problem","280033877_Recovery_of_Signals_with_Low_Density","268606869_On_a_classical_problem_of_probability_theory","268248371_Compressive_Sensing_and_Structured_Random_Matrices","266329563_A_rate_of_convergence_for_coupon_collectors","265575276_A_Mathematical_Introduction_to_Compressive_Sensing","264899823_Robust_width_A_characterization_of_uniformly_stable_and_robust_compressed_sensing","258224316_Convexity_in_Source_Separation_Models_geometry_and_algorithms","262572661_Sharp_Recovery_Bounds_for_Convex_Demixing_with_Applications","261066019_Sample-Optimal_Fourier_Sampling_in_Any_Constant_Dimension_--_Part_I","257410005_Recovering_the_Sparsest_Element_in_a_Subspace","243763676_Fourier_Analysis_on_Finite_Groups_and_Applications"]}